metadata.name: VOYAGERS #109
metadata.description:
Generative animated painting made from looping gestures in a virtual void.

Voyagers is an exploration of automated gestures and screenspace layering effects. Each brush stroke sweeps through the canvas leaving a trail of color that either disappears or mixes with adjacent colors. The image slowly builds up to achieve an equilibrium between the rhythm of the gestures and the interaction of color values. These colors are quantized and dithered to produce chunky, textured, blocks of light that reify the materiality of the screen and the pixel. Two aspect ratios are possible, each with its own material relationship to screen-based work, 1:1 and 4:3 (vertical).

Press 's' to save looping animated GIF (live mode only).
Press 'p' to pause the animation.
Press 'c' to capture a single frame.
Made with P5.js and GLSL. By @galoandstuff.

metadata.name: The Modern Depth #97
metadata.description:
there is a new horizon that shimmers and shines

a place which never was before, but there always seemed to be. 
You can see it from the top of any slope, or at the bottom any hole; you can feel it in your bones when you're tired, or be blinded by it when its bright. 
And this is why we must climb every mountain and how we'll map out all those stars. 
A shape made from Modern Depth, standing tall in front of us all.
And all the people that see it on a walk in the woods don't flinch,
they feel a strange connection to the Modern Depth that can be found. 
And most importantly, we don't abuse it because we know how to use it. Â

metadata.name: Minima #14
metadata.description:
Minima is a study on focus and color. Playing with the idea of a simple composition of semicircles, either rotated up or down. The focus of the observer is moved with the use of gradual animation in the gradients and occasional circles and/or rectangles connecting the shapes together through color.

The name minima stems from the origins of the composition, mostly taking inspiration from minimalism in its use of a few elements to form a composition greater than the sum of its parts. Less is more, as they say.

The point at the bottom right of the canvas resembles the end of a sentence. Like reading a book, you process the canvas in a similar way, moving from what pops the most to what the least.

As the reader of this canvas I hope you observe what happens to your focus as the colors gradually move across the screen. The animations themselves are looping based on a noised sine wave, which gives them imperfections, imperfections you can observe.

----

Click / Tap on the bar at the bottom of the canvas to open up the GUI, used to export your minima into any format you want. Either .png or .svg. Ready for printing, if you desire.

ps. there might be a secret keyboard shortcut...

----

Minima,
Wouter Missler, 2022,
p5js + webgl.

metadata.name: Boom_fx_max #139
metadata.description:
Boom_fx_max, by Stephen Boyd  
August, 2022  
Little India, Toronto, Canada.

This is a free mint for anyone who is a holder of Boom_fx as of August 31, 2022, 00:11:00Z. 

Signed 18" x 12" or 12" x 12" prints are available to holders for both Boom_fx and Boom_fx_max tokens on request. Please send a DM for more information.

Any unclaimed reserves will be released after four days and available at a price to be determined. 


Project Description
---
Boom_fx_max uses all eleven days of data in one image. This constitutes 4,567 earthquakes being represented in every output. This differs from the original Boom_fx which used hours of time on one of the eleven days and typically included a few hundred seismic events.

There are eleven new colour palettes and seven different ratios to organize relationships between visual elements.

The earthquake data comes from the USGS API. There is further documentation (./documentation/Information_about_boom_fx_max.md) included with this project that outlines how this data was collected and the information included in these feeds.


Three Features
---
1. Aspect ratios:
   - Landscape
   - Portrait
   - Square
2. Eleven colour palettes
3. Seven Organizing Principle Ratios:
   - Super Golden Ratio
   - PHI
   - Golden Angle
   - Silver Ratio
   - Euler's Number
   - Reciprocal Fibonacci Constant
   - Feigenbaum Constant


Interaction
---
Export to a PNG format at several different sizes.
- Press t: thumbnail @ a maximum pixel width or height of 200px
- Press s: your current screen size
- Press p: print size @ a maximum pixel width or height of 4800px which is 16"@300dpi
- Press h: HD4K on the vertical @ a maximum pixel width or height of 2160px
- Press m: Max size @ a maximum pixel width or height of 10800px.

The filename will include some metadata such as the unique hash, date and time at time of capture.


Appreciation
---
Thank you to everyone who has collected one my pieces.

Thank you to the USGS for making this data available.

And thank you the most to KIRH.


Data Sources, Software Libraries and VCS / Source Code
--- 
Data Sources
All earthquake data is sourced from the USGS Earthquake API for the International Federation of Digital Seismograph Networks (FDSN). 

Software Libraries Used
Made with Processing / P5.js  
p5.js v1.4.1 February 02, 2022
